description:
The Role
To cope with our business growth, we are looking for Fund Accountants to join our Hong Kong team.  The successful candidates will be responsible for the analysis and investment reporting for private equity and venture capital funds.



Responsibilities

Provide accounting services for clients including preparing and processing transactions and financial reports;
Provide support to clients’ investor inquires;
Prepare fee calculations (managing fees, carried interest and waterfall) verifying that calculations are in accordance with LPA;
Prepare investor capital and distribution notices;
Prepare ad hoc requests regarding fund and investor specific reports as well as analysis;
Prepare fund annual and quarterly financial reports;
Prepare SPV accounting;
Understand and assist clients with other reporting, such as FATCA, K1 etc.;
Assist clients to address and resolve audit inquiries from external auditors during year-end audit;
Participate in pre-project stage discussion with the clients and to define more detailed services model for specific clients as required;
Perform additional duties as assigned.

Requirements

Bachelor’s degree in Accounting or relevant disciplines;
2-3 year experience preferably with CPA firms working environment;
Candidate with private equity experience will be considered for senior position;
Student or associate member of CPA Australia, ACCA or equivalent qualification;
Basic knowledge of different accounting standards (IFRS, GAAPs);
Experience with RMB Fund accounting is a plus;

Other Skills

Strong organizational skills;
Ability to communicate effectively;
Good time management skills with ability to multi-task;
Fluency in both spoken and written English and Chinese (Mandarin);
Proficiency in Excel and other windows-based software;
Experience with fund accounting software solutions (Investran and Altareturn) would be highly advantageous;
Experience with Alternative investments management software (eFront) would be highly advantageous;
Knowledge of Accounting software (Kingdee, SunSystems and Quickbook, etc.) is a plus.

We offer the right candidate attractive remuneration package and outstanding prospects for career advancement and development. The right candidate will progress career in a forward thinking and dynamic business with exciting growth plans. If you are qualified and interested, please send your full resume with current & expected salary and availability by clicking "APPLY ".

All information collected will be treated as strictly confidential and used for recruitment purposes only. (Only shortlisted candidates will be notified)

One of the top 50 PE firms in Asia is hiring for an accounting and operaations officer/manager to cope with its expansion in Hong Kong. Their funds are worth about 2 billion US dollars.




Responsibilities
* Prepare quarterly reports and annual reports for venture capital funds under management ("Funds"), This will include valuation on portfolio companies of the Funds based on IFRS (fair values);
* Collaborate with inter-office investment teams on financial information of portfolio companies;
* Liaise with auditors on funds and tax advisors in respect of US K1 schedules and PFIC statements;
* Performing compliance checking and filing in respect of FATCA, CRS, FAR and US ADV (annually);
* Handle annual financial statements for Funds and annual audit of certain investment holding companies
* Assist the fund operation procedure such as capital call, distribution, management fee, bank transactions and ad-hoc tasks (for responding to investors' requests especially during fundraising period) as assigned;



Requirements:
* Degree in accounting or related disciplines with preferably 2-3 year's relevant experience in accounting
* Experience in portfolio valuation and VC/PE funds' operation will be a bonus
* Student member in HKICPA or HKICPA qualified
* Proficient in excel
* Knowledge in accounting software, such as Quickbook and investment software, such as eFront, is a plus
* Good communication skills, fluent in written English and Chinese and spoken English, Cantonese and Putonghua



* more experienced fund candidates will be given assistant manager grade

Job descriptions:

Support for performing the daily operations work, such as cash & security holding reconciliation, preparing cash forecast reporting;
Monitor the completeness of daily trade execution and matching performed by back office team;
Liaise with fund administrators, custodians and prime brokers on a daily basis;
Participate in new fund launch;
Close communication with internal departments, such as Legal & Compliance, Sales & Marketing etc;
Provide support to senior management for new project implementation.

Requirements:

Bachelor degree or above, major in finance, economics etc. preferred
Good team spirit, strong sense of responsibility, and willing to learn
Ability to pay attention to details and documents

OPIM is now accepting applications for the position of Capital Introduction Associate / Senior Associate. This is a challenging but rewarding role in a fast-paced collaborative environment. Reporting directly to the CEO and the Head of IR, you will work with the front office team to promote strategies targeting institutional allocators, corporate allocators and distributors globally. 

Your work experience in fund management and confident communication skills, a strong command of English, and affinity for helping allocators will be advantageous. You will be involving frequent client meetings/calls in which analysts assist in preparation, participation, and follow-up. Heavy in-person, phone, and e-mail interaction with hedge fund clients and allocators. 

Responsibilities: 

Prospecting for new managers and allocators;
Conducting introductory calls, coordinating and hosting new prospective allocator meetings;
Assisting in planning and execution of a range of client conferences and events, including overnight calls; 
Maintaining existing allocator relationships;
Work with the team to craft a consistent message of investment strategy;
Preparing overview materials on individual hedge fund and investor firm;
Assisting in preparing standard documents such as pitch books, investor reports, and due diligence documentation when required; 
Analyze data on the hedge fund industry and summarize key trends and themes by creating content that is distributed to allocators on a quarterly basis; 
Liaising with media channels to issue press releases of new launches and critical events; 
Coordinating with global databases and uploading fund performance; 
Updating internal Salesforce CRM for client and allocator data;
Networking and attending industry conferences; and
Coordinating ad hoc investor requests.
Requirements:

Bachelor’s degree or above; 
Up to 4 years of relevant experience (e.g, capital introduction, marketing, investor relations, allocator role, hedge fund sales); 
Self-starter with excellent attention to detail and exemplary problem-solving abilities;
Exceptional interpersonal skills; 
Energetic, efficient, and resourceful team player and individual contributor;
Detail-oriented and able to multitask, meet deadlines, and adjust to changing priorities;
Demonstrated comfort with presenting in front of both small and large groups;
Proficient computer skills including Microsoft Office suite, particularly Microsoft Excel and PowerPoint (high-level Excel and PowerPoint skills required, including experience with developing charts, pivot tables, and complex formulas);
Project Management experience is preferred; and
Fluent in spoken English, Mandarin and Cantonese.

Please apply in confidence with full resume stating your recent and expected salary to the HR Manager Ms. Carmen Lau, 9/F, The Wellington, 198 Wellington Street, Central, Hong Kong (Data collect would be used for recruitment purpose only).


Applicants who do not receive a substantive reply within two months may assume their applications unsuccessful. 

www.opim.com.hk

Responsibilities:

Research and structure new product ideas. Familiar with product design procedures, prepare legal documents for fund launching;
Understand the needs of Asset Management market, able to identify product opportunities in the market and matching to targeted customer;
Coordinate with sales team in presenting on-the-shelf products to distribution channels & targeting customers;
Assessing feasibility and profitability of various ad hoc investment proposals;

Requirements:
Minimum 1 years’ experience in finance field, preferable in renowned Asset Management Company;
Experience with offshore fund market will be an advantage;
Able to work independently with good problem solving skill and analytical mindset;
Good team player with excellent communication and interpersonal skills;
Good command of spoken and written Mandarin and English is a MUST.

Establish and strengthen the relationships with high net worth customers, identify and fulfil their investment needs by providing thorough financial analysis. Initiate and implement strategies to promote a full range of retail banking products through a proactive and professional approach in achieving the business sales targets of the bank.

Requirements:


Degree holder with at least 3 years sales experience in consumer banking field; or non-degree holder with at least 6 years consumer banking experience;
Passed in LE 1, 7, 8 or equivalent, IIQE (Paper 1, 2, 3 & 5) and MPF Intermediaries Examination is a must; holder of CFP, ARWP or CRWP qualifications will be an advantage;
Certified Banker is preferred;
Sound knowledge towards investment market and various banking products;
Sales and customer-oriented with good communication skills;
Proficient in both spoken and written English and Chinese, fluent in Putonghua is preferable.

If you are flexible enough and zeal for a harmonious and supportive working environment where enables you to grow and succeed professionally, please send a full resume indicating your public examination results (HKCEE and HKALE / HKDSE), your present and expected salary and quoting reference number attention to Talent Acquisition Division, Nanyang Commercial Bank, 151 Des Voeux Road Central, Hong Kong or apply through email. For details, please visit https://www.ncb.com.hk/ and select the page Recruit.

We are an Equal Opportunities Employer. Data collected would be used for recruitment purposes only. Applicants who do not hear from us within 8 weeks may consider their applications unsuccessful and their data will be destroyed within 12 months of receipt.

